the exploding effects of time are reversed; and the magic embryo (Firebright) is born. Thus the progressive process of the annihilation (explosion and splintering) of my Self over space and time was reversed because I saw --had seen-- something familiar in the world in 2-74: the golden fish sign, which caused enantiodromia: re-collection, reverse flow of time: it caused me to remember instead of progressively more and more forgetting and losing touch with myself; i.e. the Fall. All these regressions to the womb --and cosmogonic resorption-- and time running backward to the moment before creation --cosmogenesis-- are described by Eliade. As ways to new (second) birth; so this can be equated with the "born again" of Christianity: "only if you become like a little child can you enter the Kingdom of God." It --2-3-74-- is Taoist, alchemical, Christian, Orphic. Regression to the moment before the cosmic egg of the Orphics was ruptured and space and time --the explosion-- began (the cosmogenesis instant, recapitulated in the microcosm!). But the bottom line is: re-collection of self (anamnesis). Reversal of the primordial explosion: which unless reversed ends in total annihilation of Self (Soul); total Fall. (In all of this I acted as a microcosm of the big bang exploding macrocosm.) My concept of the re-collection of the Self is more apt than anything Eliade has come up with. It is tied in with Heidegger and Angst and Gnosticism: Sein versus das Nichts. But in me as an individual the past and future history of the entire macrocosm (universe) can be seen in terms of a titanic oscillation of original Big Bang, explosion and eventual implosion and a reversal of time, and re-collection to the primordial unity. This again suggests physics. So I "ontogenically" as microcosm recapitulated the entire "phylogenic" history of the universe in and as my own Self. Incredible as it may seem, Self explodes and becomes world and also Fremd. When the process of explosion is reversed, Self first returns as world but familiar, and then is converted (re-collected) back into Self. This explosion and becoming world and Freud means annihilation (and gives rise --reasonably-- to primal Angst). Total annihilation of the Self into the categories of world: space and time. I now know what ontological Angst is about: awareness of this explosion of Self and its conversion into world --and the Fremd. And I know what the remedy is: re-collection through anamnesis, which is based on the discovery of something familiar, something that was once a part of Self, in the world ... a very archaic part. It is as if Self-

